    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nCython is not taking into account range index. range index of list of `list[T]` is `list`. Cython expects `T`.\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\ndef main():\n    l: list[tuple] = [(1,2,3), (1,2,3)]\n    ll = l[::-1]\n    print(ll)\n\nmain()\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nCython correctly infers `list` type when range index is used.\n\n### OS\n\nLinux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.14\n\n### Cython version\n\nmaster\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
